Q1/- What is the difference between Statment and PreparedStatement?

Ans:

Statment is used when SQL query is to be executed only once.	PreparedStatement is used when SQL 
query is to be executed multiple times.


In Statment you can not pass parameters at runtime.In PreparedStatement	You can pass parameters at 
runtime.


Statment is Used for CREATE, ALTER, DROP statements.PreparedStatement is used for the queries which 
are to be executed multiple times.


 Statement Performance is very low.	Performance is better than Statement.
 
Statment  is base interface.	PreparedStatement extends statement interface.

Statment is Used to execute normal SQL queries.PreparedStatement is	used to execute dynamic SQL 
queries.
We can not use statement for reading binary data.	We can use Preparedstatement 
for reading binary data.
Statment is used for DDL statements.	PreparedStatement is used for any SQL Query.
We can not use statement for writing binary data.	We can use Preparedstatement 
for writing binary data.
In Statment No binary protocol is used for communication.In PreparedStatement Binary protocol is used
 for communication.